    <h2 align="center">Contact Us</h2>

    <p>The <i>Columbia Journalism Review</i> is recognized throughout the world as America's premier media monitor&#8212;a watchdog of the press in all its forms, from newspapers and magazines to radio, television, and cable to the wire services and the Web. Founded in 1961 under the auspices of Columbia University's Graduate School of Journalism, <i>CJR</i> examines not only day-to-day press performance but also the many forces&#8212;political, economic, technological, social, legal, and more&#8212;that affect that performance for better or worse. The magazine, which is edited by a dedicated staff of professional journalists and published six times a year, offers a mix of reporting, analysis, criticism, and commentary, always aimed at its basic goal: the continuing improvement of journalism in the service of a free society.</p>

