    <h3 align="center">Columbia Journalism Review</h3>

    <p align="center">Journalism Building<br>
    2950 Broadway<br>
    Columbia University<br>
    New York, NY 10027</p>

    <p align="center">voice: (212) 854-1881<br>
    fax: (212) 854-8580<br>
    <!--email: <a href="mailto:cjr@columbia.edu">cjr@columbia.edu</a>--></p>

    <p align="center">advertising: 212-854-3958<br>
    business: 212-854-2716<br>
    subscriptions: (toll-free in the U.S.) 888-425-7782</p>

    <h3 align="center">Writers' Guidelines</h3>

    <p>CJR accepts unsolicited queries. They can be submitted through <a href="mailto:Queries@cjr.org">email</a> or regular mail. Include a resume and a brief summary of your journalism experience and qualification to write the piece. It helps to demonstrate a familiarity with the magazine and its sections, as well as anything we have written about the subject in the past. We publish six times a year, and lead time for a piece is typically at least a month. In addition to First North American Rights, we purchase the right to publish articles on our Web site. Articles are included in academic and research databases. We pay a kill fee of half the agreed upon amount if the piece is delivered satisfactorily and then not used.</p>


